fields.name: o_PolicyKey
fields.expression:
--IIF(ISNULL(Policy_Key),IIF(ISNULL(Policy_Key1),Policy_Key2,Policy_Key1),Policy_Key)

DECODE(TRUE,
ISNULL(Policy_Key) = 0, Policy_Key,
ISNULL(Policy_Key1) = 0, Policy_Key1,
ISNULL(Policy_Key2) = 0, Policy_Key2,
ISNULL(Part_Policy_Key) = 0, Part_Policy_Key,
ISNULL(Part_Policy_Key1) = 0, Part_Policy_Key1,
Part_Policy_Key2)

fields.name: o_ClaimKey
fields.expression:
--IIF(ISNULL(Claim_Key),IIF(ISNULL(Claim_Key1),Claim_Key2,Claim_Key1),Claim_Key)


DECODE(TRUE,
ISNULL(Claim_Key) = 0, Claim_Key,
ISNULL(Claim_Key1) = 0, Claim_Key1,
ISNULL(Claim_Key2) = 0, Claim_Key2,
ISNULL(Claim_Key3) = 0, Claim_Key3,
ISNULL(Claim_Key4) = 0, Claim_Key4,
Claim_Key5)

transformations.description: This lookup procedure will find policy and claim key values based on the claim number and accident date.
transformations.name: lkp_PMS_Fact_Loss_Keys

object.customQuery:
select distinct 
    pms_fact_loss.policy_key as policy_key, 
    pms_fact_loss.claim_key as claim_key, 
    pms_fact_loss.claim_number as claim_number, 
    pms_fact_loss.accident_dt as accident_dt 
from 
    dbo.pms_fact_loss
order by  
    pms_fact_loss.claim_number, 
    pms_fact_loss.accident_dt, 
    pms_fact_loss.claim_key asc --
